# Morph showcase base mesh — octahedron crystal (compact resting state).
# Renamed from cube -> crystal in v3.0 to match the visual the player
# expects when seeing it in the "Crystals" row of the factory benchmark.
# Pairs with MorphCrystal_expanded.obj (UNIFORM 1.5x scaling, so the
# crystal "breathes" without distortion).
#
# Half-extents from center (0.5, 0.5, 0.5):
#   apex (Y)     = 0.20   →  Y range 0.30..0.70
#   equator (XZ) = 0.15   →  X/Z range 0.35..0.65
#
# Aspect ratio Y/X = 1.33 (taller than wide) preserved through morph.
#
# No named group — triangles land in model.groups (static geometry),
# which is the only path drawGroupsMorph applies per-vertex blending to.

vt 0 0
vt 1 0
vt 0.5 1

# 6 vertices: top apex, 4 equatorial (NSEW), bottom apex.
v 0.50 0.70 0.50
v 0.65 0.50 0.50
v 0.50 0.50 0.65
v 0.35 0.50 0.50
v 0.50 0.50 0.35
v 0.50 0.30 0.50

# 8 triangular faces — upper hemisphere (4) + lower hemisphere (4).
# Winding is CCW from outside POV so faces survive any cull state.
f 1/3 3/1 2/2
f 1/3 4/1 3/2
f 1/3 5/1 4/2
f 1/3 2/1 5/2
f 6/3 2/1 3/2
f 6/3 3/1 4/2
f 6/3 4/1 5/2
f 6/3 5/1 2/2
